6. Developing fluency - Respond to a text

Imagine being trapped in a smelly, tiny room surrounded 
by people you have nothing in common with except these dirty, brick walls. 
There are days we all pretend to be asleep so that 
we don‚Äôt have to engage in any conversations. We hardly speak anyway.
Instead, we tend to think a lot. 

And thinking is much worse than speaking. 
Thinking is like an extremely loud buzzing in your head. 
The kind of buzzing you fail to silence every time you try. 
In the end, you just stop trying because the trying becomes nearly 
as exhausting as the buzzing.
Regrets? I regret getting out of bed that day. 

Where is the speaker likely to be?
a prison

What does the speaker find most difficult to deal with?
her thoughts

