Tamar has a negative opinion of the text.
The main topics in the story don't resonate with Tamar.
She expects literature to make her feel positive emotions.

Watch out for "make"!
When you use "make" with another verb, the second verb doesn't change.
So "make" behaves just like "can", "should" or "might". 

It makes me feel hopeful. üëç
It makes me to feel hopeful. ‚õî
It makes me feeling hopeful. ‚õî

This book makes me cry every time I read it.

